folder: 72nd Street (East) & Madison Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
35 East 72nd Street, adjoining the N.E. corner of Madison Avenue.
About 1912.

folder: 72nd Street (East) & Madison Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
42-28 East 72nd Street, east of, adjoining, and at the S.E. corner of Madison Avenue. Pleasants Pennington and Albert W. Lewis were the architects for the building at 36 East 72nd Street, in the center of the picture.

About 1929.

folder: Madison Avenue & 72nd Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Madison Avenue, west side, north from 72nd Street, showing St. James Lutheran Church.

P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

March 28, 1929.

folder: 72nd Street (East) & Madison Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
East 72nd Street, north side, at Madison Ave. Across the clearance at the N.W. corner (formerly No. 27 East 72nd Street), appears the 13-story apartment house, No. 31-33 East 72nd Street, (at the N.E. corner).

1936.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: 72nd Street (East) & Madison Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
39 East 72nd Street, adjoining the N.E. corner of Madison Ave. Partially shown on the left is the branch bank of the Central Hanover Safe and Deposit Co. This latter structure is at the corner.

May 13, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

folder: Madison Avenue & 72nd Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)

Madison Ave., north from East 72nd Street, and showing prominently the west side with an excavation (896 and 898 Madison Ave.), at the N.W. corner of 72nd Street. The adjoining building (S.W. corner of 73rd
Street), is St. James Lutheran Church.

1936.

P. L. Sperr.
Neg.* 2398

(2)

A view of the west side of Madison Ave., between 72nd and 73rd Streets, and showing prominently the clearance at the N.W. corner of 72nd
Street.

1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)

A view of the east side of Madison Ave., and showing the Madison Ave., Presbyterian Church at the N.E. corner of East 73rd Street.

1936.

P. L. Sperr.
